-- China Retail Sales Gained 18.7% During National Day Break, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   H w e e   A n n   T a n
-- 2010-10-07T11:02:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/china-retail-sales-gained-18-7-during-national-day-break-xinhua-reports.html
Retail and catering sales in China
jumped 18.7 percent during the Oct. 1 to Oct. 7 holidays from
the same period a year ago, the official Xinhua News agency
said, citing figures from the Ministry of Commerce.  Sales reached 592.5 billion yuan, the news agency said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hwee Ann Tan at 
 hatan@bloomberg.net  